<item>
            <title>[SPARK-8506] SparkR does not provide an easy way to depend on Spark Packages when performing init from inside of R</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-8506</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While packages can be specified when using the sparkR or sparkSubmit scripts, the programming guide tells people to create their spark context using the R shell + init. The init does have a parameter for jars but no parameter for packages. Setting the SPARKR_SUBMIT_ARGS overwrites some necessary information. I think a good solution would just be adding another field to the init function to allow people to specify packages in the same way as jars.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
